OVERVIES

This project builds a complete machine learning pipeline to automatically detect spam SMS messages. Starting from raw text data, it performs data cleaning, exploratory analysis, NLP preprocessing, and trains multiple classifiers — ultimately selecting Multinomial Naive Bayes with TF-IDF features as the best model.
Metric                 Value
Dataset Size             5,572 messages
After Cleaning           5,169 messages
Training Set             4,135 (80%)
Test Set                 1,034 (20%)
Best Model               MultinomialNBBest
Accuracy                 96.9%
Precision (Spam)          98.2%

DATASET
File: spam_sms.csv
Source: UCI SMS Spam Collection Dataset
Columns:

# IN STARTING SO YOU HAVE TO CHANGE
v1 → Label (ham or spam) — renamed to Target
v2 → Raw SMS text — renamed to Text



Raw CSV Data
     │
     ▼
1. Data Cleaning        → Rename columns, encode labels, remove duplicates
     │
     ▼
2. EDA                  → Class distribution, character/word/sentence analysis
     │
     ▼
3. Text Preprocessing   → Lowercase → Tokenize → Remove noise → Remove stopwords → Stem
     │
     ▼
4. Feature Extraction   → TF-IDF Vectorizer (max_features=3000)
     │
     ▼
5. Model Training       → GaussianNB, MultinomialNB, BernoulliNB, Logistic Regression, Decision Tree
     │
     ▼
6. Evaluation           → Accuracy, Precision, Confusion Matrix
     │
     ▼
7. Save Model           → vectorizer.pkl + model.pkl


